{{Speciesbox | image = | status = | status_system = | status_ref = | taxon = Drombus bontii | authority = ([[Pieter Bleeker|Bleeker]], 1849) | synonyms = * ''Acentrogobius bontii'' <small>(Bleeker, 1849)</small> * ''Gobius bontii'' <small>(Bleeker, 1849)</small> }}
'''''Drombus bontii''''' is a [[species]] of [[goby]] native to the [[Indian Ocean]] from the [[Bazaruto Archipelago]] of [[Mozambique]] through to the [[tropical]] waters of the western [[Pacific Ocean]]. This species can reach a length of {{convert|7.1|cm|in}} [[fish measurement|TL]]. The status of this species is questionable, with [[Maurice Kottelat]] considering it to be a junior [[Synonym (taxonomy)|synonym]] of ''[[Drombus triangularis]]''.<ref>{{FishBase |genus= Gobius|species= bontii| month = June | year = 2013}}</ref><ref name="kottelat">{{cite book|author1=Maurice Kottelat|author2=A. J. Whitten|author3=S. N. Kartikasari|author4=S. Wirjoatmodjo|last-author-amp=yes|year=1993|title=Freshwater fishes of Western Indonesia and Sulawesi|publisher=Periplus Editions, Hong Kong|isbn=0945971605}}</ref>
