'''Picarin''' is a [[plastic]] used to make optics such as [[lens (optics)|lens]]es for [[terahertz radiation]] (THz radiation). Picarin is useful for this purpose because it is highly [[transparency (optics)|transparent]] in both the THz and [[visible light|visible]] [[spectrum|spectral]] ranges. The [[refractive index]] of Picarin is almost the same for THz (''n''=1.52) and visible light (''n''=1.52). It is very strong mechanically, and withstands optical [[polishing]].<ref name="mtinstruments">http://www.mtinstruments.com - dealer</ref>

'''Unpolished Picarin Lenses''' offer the best performance at 2-7 THz spectral range. Unfortunately, unpolished surfaces scatter visible and near-IR light.<ref name="mtinstruments"/>

A version which can be polished is sold as '''Tsurupica'''.<ref name="bblaser">http://www.bblaser.com - producer (not English)</ref>

