A '''shock stall''' is a [[Stall (flight)|stall]] created when the [[airflow]] over an [[aircraft]]'s [[wing]]s is disturbed by [[shock waves]] formed when flying at or above the aircraft's [[drag divergence Mach number]].

A '''stall''' is the decrease in Lift to a value below the Weight, and the associated increase in Drag upon the separation of the boundary layer (in this case behind the shock wave).

